# Angular Signal Forms — Common Pitfalls & Troubleshooting

## Critical Mistakes Table

| Mistake | WRONG | CORRECT |
|---------|-------|---------|
| Access field state | `form.field.valid()` | `form.field().valid()` |
| Access field value | `form.field.value()` | `form.field().value()` |
| Set field value | `form.field.set('x')` | `this.model.update(m => ({...m, field: 'x'}))` |
| Root form state | `form.invalid()` | `form().invalid()` |
| Double-calling | `form.field()()` | `form.field().value()` |
| Rules context | `({ touched }) => touched()` | `({ state }) => state.touched()` |
| Calling paths in schema | `s.foo()` inside schema | `valueOf(s.foo)` from context |
| applyWhen args | `applyWhen(condition, () => {...})` | `applyWhen(path, condition, schemaFn)` — 3 args |
| Array length | `form.items().length` | `form.items.length` (structural) |
| Multi-select arrays | `<select [formField]="form.tags">` (string[]) | `<select multiple [formField]="form.tags">` |
| readonly attribute | `<input readonly [formField]="...">` | Use `readonly()` rule in schema |
| min/max attributes | `<input min="18" [formField]="...">` | Use `min()` / `max()` rules in schema |
| value binding | `<input [value]="x" [formField]="...">` | Do NOT use `[value]` with `[formField]` |
| `when` option | `pattern(s.x, /.../, {when: ...})` | `when` only works with `required()` |
| Submit callback | `submit(form, () => { ... })` | `submit(form, async () => { ... })` |
| Async params | `params: s.field` | `params: ({ value }) => value()` |
| Async onError | Omitting `onError` | `onError` is REQUIRED in `validateAsync` |
| resource() API | `request: signal` | `params: signal` |
| applyEach args | `applyEach(s.items, (item, index) => ...)` | `applyEach(s.items, (item) => ...)` — 1 arg |
| Nested @for | `$parent.$index` | Use `let outerIdx = $index` |
| FormState import | `import { FormState }` | `FormState` does NOT exist |
| Null in model | `signal({ name: null })` | `signal({ name: '' })` |
| Validate syntax | `validate(s.field, { value } => ...)` | `validate(s.field, ({ value }) => ...)` |
| Checkbox array | `[formField]="form.tags"` (string[]) | Checkboxes ONLY bind to `boolean` |
| Validator return | `return null` | Prefer `return undefined` |

## Build Error Fixes

### `Property 'value' does not exist on type 'FieldTree'`

You're accessing state without calling the field first:

```ts
// WRONG
const val = this.form.field.value();
// CORRECT
const val = this.form.field().value();
```

### `Property 'set' does not exist on type 'FieldTree'`

Signal Forms are model-driven. Update the model signal, not the form:

```ts
// WRONG
this.form.address.street.set('Main St');
// CORRECT
this.model.update(m => ({ ...m, address: { ...m.address, street: 'Main St' } }));
```

### `Type 'string[]' is not assignable to type 'string'`

Binding `[formField]` to an array field with a single-value `<select>`:

```html
<!-- WRONG -->
<select [formField]="form.assignees">...</select>

<!-- CORRECT — use select multiple for array fields -->
<select multiple [formField]="form.assignees">
  <option value="a">A</option>
</select>
```

### `NG8022: Setting the 'readonly/min/max/value' attribute is not allowed`

Remove conflicting HTML attributes and use schema rules instead:

```html
<!-- WRONG -->
<input [formField]="form.age" min="18" max="99" />

<!-- CORRECT -->
<input [formField]="form.age" />
<!-- Use in schema: min(s.age, 18); max(s.age, 99); -->
```

### `TS2322: Type 'string[]' is not assignable to type 'boolean'`

Binding a checkbox to an array field:

```html
<!-- WRONG — tags is string[] -->
<input type="checkbox" [formField]="form.tags" />

<!-- CORRECT — use select multiple -->
<select multiple [formField]="form.tags">
  <option value="a">A</option>
</select>

<!-- OR map to boolean fields -->
<!-- model = signal({ hasWifi: false, hasGym: false }) -->
<input type="checkbox" [formField]="form.hasWifi" />
```

### `'when' does not exist in type` for pattern/email/min/max

`when` ONLY works with `required()`. Use `applyWhen` for conditional non-required validators:

```ts
// WRONG
pattern(s.ssn, /^\d{3}-\d{2}-\d{4}$/, { when: isJoint });

// CORRECT
applyWhen(s.ssn, isJoint, (ssnPath) => {
  pattern(ssnPath, /^\d{3}-\d{2}-\d{4}$/);
});
```

### `Expected 3 arguments, but got 2` for applyWhen

Missing the path argument:

```ts
// WRONG
applyWhen(isJoint, () => { ... });

// CORRECT — applyWhen(path, condition, schemaFn)
applyWhen(s.spouse, ({ valueOf }) => valueOf(s.status) === 'joint', (spousePath) => {
  required(spousePath.name);
});
```

### `Module has no exported member 'FormState'`

`FormState` does not exist. Access state through calling the field:

```ts
// WRONG
import { FormState } from '@angular/forms/signals';

// CORRECT — just use the field
const state = this.myForm.email(); // This IS the FieldState
state.valid();
state.touched();
```

### `No pipe found with name 'number'` / `'json'` / `'date'`

Pipes need to be imported or use computed:

```html
<!-- WRONG (if pipe not imported) -->
{{ totalPrice() | number:'1.2-2' }}

<!-- CORRECT — format in the component -->
totalPriceFormatted = computed(() => this.totalPrice().toFixed(2));
<!-- then: -->
{{ totalPriceFormatted() }}
```

### `$parent.$index` in nested @for loops

Angular doesn't have `$parent`:

```html
<!-- WRONG -->
@for (item of items; track $index) {
  @for (sub of item.subs; track $index) {
    <button (click)="remove($parent.$index, $index)">X</button>
  }
}

<!-- CORRECT -->
@for (item of items; track $index; let outerIdx = $index) {
  @for (sub of item.subs; track $index) {
    <button (click)="remove(outerIdx, $index)">X</button>
  }
}
```

## Key Behavioral Notes

### Schema Function Runs Once

The schema function runs **only once** during form creation. Do NOT use dynamic `if` statements to conditionally call binding functions. Use `applyWhen` instead.

### Validation Doesn't Short-Circuit

All validation rules run — validation doesn't stop after the first error. Multiple errors can coexist.

### Validation Order

1. Synchronous rules run on every value change
2. Async rules run only after ALL sync rules pass
3. Field state signals update

### Hidden/Disabled Fields Skip Validation

When a field is `hidden` or `disabled`, validation rules don't run.

### Touched on Blur

`touched()` becomes `true` when a user focuses AND blurs a field through user interaction (not programmatically). Disabled/hidden fields don't become touched.

### State Propagation

- `valid()` on a parent is `true` only if ALL descendants are valid
- `touched()` on a parent is `true` if ANY descendant is touched
- `dirty()` on a parent is `true` if ANY descendant is dirty
- `disabled()` on a child is `true` if the child OR any ancestor is disabled

### Never Reassign the Model Signal

```ts
// WRONG — form still points to old signal
this.model = signal(newData);

// CORRECT — update the existing signal
this.model.set(newData);
this.model.update(m => ({ ...m, ...newData }));
```

### linkedSignal for Readonly Signals

If your source is a readonly signal (e.g., from NgRx `selectSignal()`), wrap with `linkedSignal()`:

```ts
import { linkedSignal } from '@angular/core';

readonly source = this.store.selectSignal(selectUser);
readonly model = linkedSignal(this.source);
readonly userForm = form(this.model, /* ... */);
```

## Testing Tips

- Provide an injector when creating forms in tests:
  ```ts
  form(model, schema, { injector: TestBed.inject(Injector) });
  ```
- Use `model.set()` / `model.update()` to simulate value changes
- Use `field.$state.value.set()` to simulate user input
- Check `field.$state.errors()`, `field.$state.valid()` for assertions
